{{Infobox piercing | name = Anal piercing | nicknames = | image =Perianal ring piercing in human female.jpg | image_size = 200px | location = [[Anus]] | jewelry = [[Captive bead ring]], [[barbell (piercing)|barbell]] | healing time = }}
An '''anal piercing''' is a [[body piercing]] in the surrounding area of the [[human anus]], usually the [[perineum]].<ref name="Angel2011">{{cite book|author=Elayne Angel|title=The Piercing Bible: The Definitive Guide to Safe Body Piercing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=83sjmTPnz48C&pg=PA25|date=16 February 2011|publisher=Potter/TenSpeed/Harmony|isbn=978-0-307-77791-1|pages=25–}}</ref>
Despite the name, piercing of the anal sphincter itself is rather rare. Some report difficulty cleaning the area after defecation and increases chances of infection.<ref name="Angel2011"/>
In the [[United Kingdom]] the minimum age for an anal piercing is 16 enacted in the Sexual Offense Act of 2003.<ref name="Allen2015">{{cite book|author=Tony Allen|title=Age Restricted Sales: The Law in England and Wales|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2GBDCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA178|date=28 October 2015|publisher=Troubador Publishing Ltd|isbn=978-1-78462-419-4|pages=178–}}</ref>
Historically, anal piercings have been used as a form of humiliation.<ref name="Stoichita2000">{{cite book|author=Victor I. Stoichita|title=Goya: The Last Carnival|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mZfxAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA95|date=1 January 2000|publisher=Reaktion Books|isbn=978-1-86189-666-7|pages=95–}}</ref>
